Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 3cm pieces. Trim the @carrot{2} (no need to peel) and cut into batons about the size of your index finger. Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Halve and peel the @echalion shallot{1}. Cut each half lengthways into quarters.

Pop the potatoes onto one #large baking tray{} and the rest of the veg onto another. Add the whole @garlic clove{1} (still in its skin!) onto the tray with the potatoes. Add a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} to both trays. Drizzle over some @olive oil{}. Toss to coat everything well, then pop the potatoes onto top shelf of the oven and the rest of the veg onto the middle shelf. Cook until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through and remove the garlic cloves.

Meanwhile, sprinkle the @ground cumin{2%tsp} over the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} and add a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub everything in to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Pop the chicken into the pan (skin-side down). Cook until the skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn over and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Pop onto the potato tray (skin-side up) and cook for the final ~{15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle!

== Garlic Yogurt Dressing ==

In the meantime, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(chopped roughly, stalks and all). Pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g} into a #small bowl{}. Add the juice from half the lemon and the @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Once the garlic cloves are cool enough to handle, squeeze the garlic from its skin, mash with a #fork{} or grate into the dressing (or use a #garlic press{}).

> TIP: Add the garlic to taste, you don't have to use it all! Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Once the veggies are out of the oven and the chicken is cooked, pop all the veggies (including the potatoes) into a #large mixing bowl{} along with half the coriander, the lemon zest and any cooking juices from the chicken. Toss to combine. Thinly slice the chicken.

Divide the roasted vegetables between your plates and place the chicken on top. Drizzle over the yogurt dressing and sprinkle over the remaining coriander. Serve with the remaining lemon, chopped into wedges, for squeezing over. Enjoy!